As I mentioned in [my comment](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58513780/how-to-deal-with-underflow-in-java/58513821#comment103354738_58513780), `1.0665901062490447E-18` is a **very** small value. If you need that much precision, you should be using [`BigDecimal`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/math/BigDecimal.html). Something like,

	double a = 1.0665901062490447E-18, b = 1.0;
	System.out.println(BigDecimal.valueOf(a).add(BigDecimal.valueOf(b)).toPlainString());

Which outputs

    1.0000000000000000010665901062490447

Note that there is a predefined constant [`BigDecimal.ONE`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/math/BigDecimal.html#ONE) - so the above could also be written

	System.out.println(BigDecimal.valueOf(a).add(BigDecimal.ONE).toPlainString());

