answers.body_markdown:
The [`SynchronizationLockException`][1] is thrown because between these two lines:

    Monitor.Wait(processingText);
    //...
    Monitor.PulseAll(processingText);

...the value of the variable `processingText` has changed. So the [`Monitor.PulseAll`][2] tries to send a pulse using a lock that is not owned by the current thread, hence the exception you observe.

  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.threading.synchronizationlockexception
  [2]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.threading.monitor.pulseall

